To update your database schema, you need to add a new `Tag` model and a relation between `Listing` and `Tag`. Here's how you can do it:

```prisma
model Tag {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  name      String   @unique
  listings  Listing[] @relation("TagToListing")
}

model Listing {
  // existing fields...
  tags      Tag[]    @relation("TagToListing")
}
```

In the `Tag` model, `name` is the name of the tag (e.g., "industrial", "ux/ui"). The `listings` field represents the many-to-many relation between `Tag` and `Listing`.

In the `Listing` model, the `tags` field represents the other side of the many-to-many relation.

After updating the schema, you need to run the Prisma migration command to update your database:

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev --name add-tags
```

Then, you need to write a script to migrate the old disciplines to the new tags. Here's a rough idea of how you can do it:

```javascript
const prisma = new PrismaClient();

async function migrateDisciplinesToTags() {
  const listings = await prisma.listing.findMany();

  for (const listing of listings) {
    for (const discipline of listing.disciplines) {
      let tag = await prisma.tag.findUnique({ where: { name: discipline } });

      if (!tag) {
        tag = await prisma.tag.create({ data: { name: discipline } });
      }

      await prisma.listing.update({
        where: { id: listing.id },
        data: { tags: { connect: { id: tag.id } } },
      });
    }
  }
}

migrateDisciplinesToTags().finally(() => prisma.$disconnect());
```

